==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pixie
<hw>Pix"ie</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Pixies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[For <ets>Pucksy</ets>, from <ets>Puck</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>An old English name for a fairy; an elf.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>picksy</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A low creeping evergreen plant
(<spn>Pyxidanthera barbulata</spn>), with mosslike leaves and little
white blossoms, found in New Jersey and southward, where it flowers in
earliest spring.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pixy ring</b></col>, <cd>a fairy ring or circle.</cd>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark> -- <col><b>Pixy stool</b></col>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>a toadstool or mushroom.</cd> <mark>[Prov.
Eng.]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pixy-led</ent>⟦br⟧
